      <abstract>
        <p>We describe a case of morphea which presented further typical lesions of the disease at the sites of mechanical trauma. It can be suggested that cutaneous lesions of morphea may be locally developed due to physical stimuli as an isomorphic response in patients or subclinical cases of the disease.</p>
